OL,3,CLabour MP calls for more changes to
OL,4,CHillsborough Law to get rid of
OL,5,C'loopholes'
OL,7,FMPs had been due to debate the
OL,8,FHillsborough Law on 14 January but the
OL,9,Fdiscussion was pushed back until 19
OL,10,FJanuary to allow the Government to
OL,11,Fpropose changes that might address
OL,12,Fcampaigners' concerns.
OL,14,FSome had warned that a draft version
OL,15,Fof the legislation ` formally known as
OL,16,Fthe Public Office (Accountability)
OL,17,FBill ` might allow intelligence chiefs
OL,18,Fto "hide serious failures behind a
OL,19,Fvague claim of national security".
OL,26,@zD@DOU{D@aO]
